content: On screen buttons are very poor, turn rate ridiculous
replyContent: Hi and thank you for playing the game and also for your honest review. You will will probably prefer the second control scheme. Just go into the settings to change it. Also, if you have a bluetooth controller such as an Xbox joypad, it works great with that too, and also with both styles of settings. Best of luck and kind regards Zephiroth Games

content: Excellent, graphics and sound just like the arcade game. I must admit I wasn't enjoying it as much at first, using the on-screen controls the ship rotation isn't accurate enough. But after pairing a Bluetooth game pad it's brilliant (use the second control option). Yes, the gameplay is slightly faster than the original, but that just makes it more frenetic and challenging!! Just two requests:- 1) option to turn off the on-screen controls for gamepad users. 2) where's the hyperspace feature?

The best early arcade game is back and almost better than the original! Authentic play and sound effects, but with a virtual joystick mode for those of us that could never quite master the left / right / thrust button combo (though there's button mode too if you want true authenticity). The only thing missing is hyperspace, and given the rez that isn't needed. Both saucer sizes are here tho, & if it had the 'pa-POW' sound of the original large saucer this would actually be the perfect game.
replyContent: Hi and thanks for reviewing the game. Please note the smaller saucers come on later levels. Kind regards, Zephiroth Games

content: Finally! A true authentic feel to a classic arcade game. Definitely worthy of the name unlike others out there adding in their own unnecessary touches... Please add Google Play Services like Leaderboards/Achievements to keep track of records and high scores among other players

This game needs auto rapid firing not just tapping manually on the fire button. Also needs exiting out when pressing on back button! Please enable my requests... Then you will receive my all five star rating. Thanks!
Very much like the old arcade game in every way. The motion of the ship, how it changes orientation and accelerates and fires missiles; how the asteroids fly apart and move; even the sound effects!
I used to play Asteroids all the time as a kid. This looks, plays, and feels just like the original. Awesome!

Just like the arcade game, at least as I remember it. Unfortunately, no option to quit the app and it disables the soft buttons (home, back) on my Sony Xperia Z5, so once you start there's no stopping... Fix that and it's a 5* app.

About 3 years ago I played a great vector game called Mars Lander TD, it was not updated to work with q hd screens unfortunately. This is obviously an arcade remake, but has the same feel and awsome sound effects. Needs an exit please. Galaxy s6 on andriod 6
